### 3. TECH STACK

**Frontend**: Pure vanilla HTML/CSS/JS. Zero build toolchain. No Node.js, no bundler, no framework.
- **CSS**: Single file `css/styles.css` (360 lines), CSS custom properties for theming (light/dark)
- **JS**: 6 hand-written files, loaded via `<script>` tags. IIFE pattern, no modules.
- **Data**: Loaded from `window.BRANDS`, `window.STORES`, `window.PHONES`, `window.NEWS`, `window.SPECS` globals set by data.js and specs-data.js
- **Fonts**: Inter (system-ui fallback)
- **Comments**: Giscus (GitHub Discussions-backed)
- **External services**: Brandfetch CDN (brand logos), Simple Icons CDN, open.er-api.com (currency rates), ipwho.is (geo detection), Lorem Picsum (fallback news images)

**Backend/Pipeline**: Python 3.x, stdlib only (no pip packages).
- No `package.json`, no `requirements.txt` -- pure Python scripts.

**Hosting**: GitHub Pages (static). Deploy triggered by GitHub Actions.

---

### 4. DATA ARCHITECTURE AND PIPELINE

**Pipeline entry point**: `tools/run_all.py` (line 25-35)

Execution order (5 stages):

| Stage | Script | Purpose | Input | Output |
|-------|--------|---------|-------|--------|
| 1 | `import_specs.py` | Pull specs from phone-specs-API | Live API (config `specs_api_base`) | `data/specs.json` |
| 1b | `wikidata_seed.py` | Seed catalog from Wikidata SPARQL | Wikidata (free, unlimited) | Merges into `data/specs.json` |
| 1c | `seed_dataset.py` | Seed from static GSMArena dataset | Local JSON file | Overwrites `data/specs.json` |
| 2 | `content_agent.py` | AI-generated reviews/pros/cons/ratings | `data/specs.json` + LLM API | `data/content.json` (cached) |
| 3 | `price_job.py` | Affiliate links + optional PA-API prices | `data/specs.json` | `data/prices.json` |
| 4 | `news_fetch.py` | Aggregate tech news | HN, RSS, Reddit, NewsAPI | `data/news.json` |
| 5 | `build.py` | Merge all caches into frontend files | All `data/*.json` | `js/data.js`, `js/specs-data.js`, `tools/data/merged.json` |
| 5a | `prerender.py` | Static HTML per phone | `data/merged.json` | `phone/*.html` (~1411 pages) |
| 5b | `gen_images.py` | SVG fallback images | `data/merged.json` | `img/*.svg` (~1411 files) |
| 5c | `gen_seo.py` | Sitemap + robots.txt | `js/data.js` | `sitemap.xml`, `robots.txt` |
| 5d | `indexnow.py` | Ping search engines | `sitemap.xml` | IndexNow API call |

**Data flow**: Source APIs --> `data/specs.json` --> enrich with AI content + prices + news --> `data/merged.json` --> `js/data.js` + `phone/*.html` + `sitemap.xml`

**Data model per product** (from `build.py` lines 74-93):
- `id`, `brand`, `name`, `category` (phone/tablet/laptop/tv/smartwatch/earbuds/headphones/camera/console/appliance/auto)
- `image`, `images[]`, `fallbackImg` (local SVG path)
- `releaseDate`, `basePrice`, `popularity` (40-99), `rating` (3.0-5.0), `reviewCount`
- `review` (AI-generated text), `pros[]`, `cons[]` (AI-generated)
- `quickSpecs` (display, processor, ram, storage, camera, battery)
- `prices[]` (store, price, url with affiliate tag)
- `specs` (nested sections -> key-value pairs, full spec sheets)

**Brand model** (from `ph_common.py` lines 16-560):
- `id`, `name`, `logo` (Brandfetch/SimpleIcons CDN URL), `color` (hex), `category` (Premium/Mid-Range/Value/Budget/Gaming/Auto/Other)
- **130+ brands** in BRAND_DATABASE, including ~70 car brands, ~30 tech/electronics brands, and obscure/vintage brands

